headline: The Cigna Group Foundation Announces First Grantee Cohort of Health Equity Impact Fund
summary: The Cigna Group Foundation, the philanthropic arm of The Cigna Group (NYSE: CI), announced today the first round of grant recipients – comprised of 15 nonprofits across Hartford, CT, and Houston, TX – for The Cigna Group Health Equity Impact Fund. Through this new program, The Cigna Group Foundation will allocate $9 million to nonprofit organizations over the next three years as part of its continuing focus on reducing health disparities.
